  "description": "Each major arcana card lists a short interpretation. Upright and reversed are sketches to be adapted to context.\n¶The Fool Upright: beginnings, openness, risk. Reversed: hesitation, naivete, avoidance.\n¶The Magician Upright: will, skill, initiative. Reversed: manipulation, scattered focus.\n¶The High Priestess Upright: intuition, hidden knowledge. Reversed: blocked intuition, secrecy.\n¶The Empress Upright: nurture, growth, abundance. Reversed: stagnation, overindulgence.\n",
